    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I don't know if it helps debugging, but on both Chrome and IE, zooming in or out (+/- 10% on Chrome, 105% & 85% on IE) makes the horizontal scrollbar disappear. Additionally if the horizontal scrollbar actually scrolls (i.e. the line is longer than the cell width), the scrollbar behaves properly and shows below the text instead of blocking it.\n\nChrome: 36.0.1985.18 beta-m\nIE: 11.0.9600.17107\n\nTL;DR: one workaround is to zoom in or out a bit.\n"
